$ HTML: DOCTYPE declaration

The ~DOCTYPE declaration~ of a → development/web/HTML document defines the defines the *document type* of a webpage wich in turn
controls the → development/web/browser/layout-engine[layout mode] in which a → development/web/browser renders the document.

In order to render a document in *full standard mode*, the following DOCTYPE declaration needs to be put at the start of a HTML document:
code {
<!DOCTYPE html>
code }

If there is *anything* before the `<!DOCTYPE html>` declaration, the document will be assumed to be in quirks mode.

sa:
  → development/web/HTML/tags

links:
  MDN: → https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Quirks_Mode_and_Standards_Mode[Quirks Mode and Standards Mode]
